revised_title: Marsipohranch Fishes Skeleton: Part II - Petromyzon
tldr: The author examines the skeleton of Marsipohranch fishes, specifically Petromyzon, in various stages of development. They describe the composition and structure of the cartilage, the cranial and vertebral development, and the facial outgrowths. The study provides insights into the evolution and morphology of these fish species.
scientific_discipline: Biology and Life Sciences > Vertebrate Anatomy
